# Jira06 - FINAL: UI Automated Test with Selenium NUnit (C#)

## Project Overview

This project is an **automated UI testing framework** built using:

- NUnit (Test Framework)
- Selenium WebDriver
- C# 
- ExtentReports (Test reporting)
- JSON Test Data Driven

The purpose is to automate test scenarios for: https://demoqa.com/

---

## Tech Stack

| Component | Technology |
|----------|------------|
| Language | C# |
| Framework | NUnit |
| UI Automation | Selenium WebDriver |
| Reporting | ExtentReports |
| Test Data | JSON |
| Target App | https://demoqa.com/ |


---

## Test Scenarios

---

## Scenario 1.1: Register student with all fields successfully

### Given
- User is on Student Registration Form page

### When
- User inputs valid data into all fields
- User clicks Submit button

### Then
- Successful message **"Thanks for submitting the form"** is displayed
- All submitted information is shown correctly

---

## Scenario 1.2: Register student with mandatory fields successfully

### Given
- User is on Student Registration Form page

### When
- User inputs valid data into required fields only
- User clicks Submit button

### Then
- Successful message **"Thanks for submitting the form"** is displayed
- All mandatory information is shown correctly

---

## Scenario 2: Search book with multiple results

### Given
- User is on Book Store page https://demoqa.com/books

### When
- User searches book name: **"Design"** or **"design"**

### Then
- All matching books are displayed correctly

---

## Scenario 3: Delete book successfully

### Given
- A book named **"Git Pocket Guide"** exists
- User is logged into the application
- User is on Profile page

### When
- User searches for the book
- User clicks Delete icon
- User confirms deletion (OK)
- User confirms alert “Book deleted.”

### Then
- Book is removed from the list


